# Compile each parsed invariant into a TestPlan — Architecture doc Section 7.1 (invariant grammar portability)
#
# Fan-out note: InvariantParser/parse => ok returns `invariants: String` — a JSON array of invariant
# identifiers, not a single identifier. Clef's sync grammar does not provide a native "one then per
# item in a collection" dispatch within a then-clause. The approach taken here is to dispatch a single
# TestPlan/build call with the full JSON array and let TestPlan iterate internally.
# If TestPlan/build later gains a `buildBatch(invariants: String)` action this sync should be updated
# to use that action name to make the intent explicit. Until then, TestPlan/build receives
# `invariantId` bound to the full `?invs` JSON array and is expected to detect the array shape and
# iterate. This is a known grammar limitation tracked in the invariant grammar portability PRD (MAG-908).

sync BuildTestPlanOnInvariantParse [eager]
  purpose {
    After InvariantParser/parse completes, compile every extracted invariant into an enriched
    platform-agnostic TestPlan. Dispatches TestPlan/build with the full invariant-ids payload
    so TestPlan can iterate over them internally (Clef has no native per-item then fan-out).
  }
when {
  InvariantParser/parse: [ specKind: ?kind; sourceRef: ?src ]
    => ok(invariants: ?invs)
}
then {
  TestPlan/build: [
    invariantId: ?invs
  ]
}
